cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.CG

This paper deals with the problem of routing packets on the Internet, which is a fundamental problem in computer networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a new algorithm for routing packets based on a global Internet map, which involves the use of hyperbolic geometry. This suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed algorithm in terms of speed and robustness, which could make it relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
